  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Dice the <strong>sweet&nbsp;potatoes </strong>(skins on)&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>diced sweet potatoes</strong> to a baking tray, drizzle them with<strong>&nbsp;vegetable oil</strong>&nbsp;and scatter the&nbsp;<strong>smoked paprika </strong>over</p>\r\n<p>Season them with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and put the tray in the oven for 30 min or until cooked through and crispy</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the<strong> red&nbsp;</strong><strong>pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half and deseed (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon)&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Dice the<strong> tomato<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong><span class=\"text-danger\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop the<strong> shallot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong>&nbsp;halved peppers</strong> to a baking tray and stuff them with the<strong>&nbsp;diced tomato </strong>and&nbsp;half of the<strong> chopped shallot</strong></p>\r\n<p>Drizzle them with the&nbsp;<strong>red wine vinegar</strong></p>\r\n<p>Season them with a pinch of both <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and drizzle generously with <strong>olive oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until they have softened and wrinkled at the edges - these are your <strong>sweet and sour peppers&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the<strong> garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Chop the <strong>parsley</strong> finely,&nbsp;including the stalks&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped parsley</strong> to a <strong>pestle and mortar</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Grind to a paste, then add the<strong>&nbsp;chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> Dijon mustard</strong> and remaining<strong>&nbsp;chopped shallot</strong></p>\r\n<p>Stir in 3-4 tbsp <strong>olive oil</strong>&nbsp;- this is your <strong>salsa verde&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/947.-step-5-x200.jpg",
